item.title: Competition Periods
item.description: Introduction A VEX Robotics Competition match is 2 minutes long, split into two different time periods: Autonomous Period (15 seconds) and Driver Controlled Period (1 minute 45 seconds). During the Autonomous Period, robots operate without any help from humans using pre-programmed commands and sensor inputs. During the Driver Controlled Period, humans can operate their robots via remote control. How does the robot know when it is Autonomous or Driver Controlled Period?
